RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 12 1M Turf CR: 88. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $25,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $25,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYALTY INTEREST (FR) raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn, kicked clear in the stretch and drew off in the final furlong. LIL MISS MOONLIGHT raced in the four path around the first turn, tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far bend, dueled in upper stretch and chased the winner to the wire from there. JUSTIFIABLE BELLE bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, stumbling slightly in the process, recovered to chase the leader on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path, raced into traffic and switched to the outside in upper and improved position late. VOLATILITY saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and gained ground late. GALILEO'S JEWEL (IRE) bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, raced in the three path around the first bend, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the far turn and weakened in the stretch. MYSTERIOUS STARE led the way from the two path around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend and faded in the lane. GOTHAM GRAY raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, navigated the far turn still in the three path and showed no kick. LANCE'S SMILE raced in the four path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and made no bid. DOUBLE SCOOP (IRE) raced off the pace in the three path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the second turn and was empty in the lane. AL TIRAH trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Gotham Gray
ENTRY.OWNER: Adelphi Racing Club Backstretch Seven Racing and Oak Hill Thoroughbred LLC
